{
  "info": {
    "name": "Auth API with Auto Token Management",
    "description": "Complete authentication API collection with automatic token management for all requests. Get token once, use everywhere!",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [
      {
        "key": "token",
        "value": "{{authToken}}",
        "type": "string"
      }
    ]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "üîê AUTHENTICATION",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "1. Request OTP",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/request-otp",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "request-otp"]
            },
            "description": "Step 1: Request OTP code\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Enter your email in the body\n2. Press Send\n3. Check the console output for OTP code\n4. In dev mode, OTP is always: **123456**"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "2. Verify OTP & Get Token",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const responseData = pm.response.json();",
                  "    ",
                  "    // Save token to environment variable",
                  "    pm.environment.set('authToken', responseData.token);",
                  "    ",
                  "    // Also save to collection variable for persistence",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('authToken', responseData.token);",
                  "    ",
                  "    // Save user info",
                  "    pm.environment.set('userId', responseData.user.id);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('userEmail', responseData.user.email);",
                  "    pm.environment.set('isNewUser', responseData.isNewUser);",
                  "    ",
                  "    console.log('‚úÖ Authentication successful!');",
                  "    console.log('üìù Token saved to {{authToken}}');",
                  "    console.log('üë§ User ID: ' + responseData.user.id);",
                  "    console.log('üìß Email: ' + responseData.user.email);",
                  "    console.log('üÜï New User: ' + responseData.isNewUser);",
                  "    ",
                  "    pm.test('Authentication successful', function () {",
                  "        pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.equal(200);",
                  "        pm.expect(responseData).to.have.property('token');",
                  "        pm.expect(responseData).to.have.property('user');",
                  "    });",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"user@example.com\",\n  \"otp\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["auth", "verify-otp"]
            },
            "description": "Step 2: Verify OTP and get JWT token\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Use the same email from Step 1\n2. Enter OTP: **123456** (in dev mode)\n3. Press Send\n4. ‚úÖ Token will be automatically saved!\n\n**After this step:**\n- Token is stored in `{{authToken}}`\n- You can now call all protected APIs\n- Token is automatically added to all requests"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
